-- Alam Sutera Realty, Bakrie & Brothers: Indonesia Equity Preview
-- B y   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a
-- 2011-12-19T01:51:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-19/alam-sutera-realty-bakrie-brothers-indonesia-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have  unusual (JCI)  moves in Indonesian trading. Stock symbols are
in parentheses, and share prices are as of the previous close.  The Jakarta Composite index rose 1.8 percent to 3,768.35.  Coal producers: Power-station coal  prices  at Australia’s
Newcastle port, an Asian benchmark, fell 1.1 percent to $110.28
a metric ton in the week ended Dec. 16.  PT Bumi Resources (BUMI)  , Asia’s largest exporter of
power-station coal, was unchanged at 2,250 rupiah and  PT Adaro
Energy (ADRO)  , Indonesia’s second-largest coal producer, rose
1.1 percent to 1,840 rupiah.  PT Alam Sutera Realty (ASRI)  : The property developer
plans to invest 3 trillion rupiah ($330 million) in 2012 to
boost business expansion, Investor Daily Indonesia reported
citing, President Director Tri Ramadi. The company may sell $200
million of global bonds to help finance its business next year,
the report said. Alam Sutera advanced 2.2 percent to 460 rupiah.  PT Bakrie & Brothers (BNBR)  : The investment company may
sell 1 trillion rupiah of bonds in the first quarter of next
year to refinance debt, Finance Director Eddy Soeparno said.
Bakrie expects revenue to rise as much as 25 percent next year,
Soeparno also said. The stock was unchanged at 51 rupiah.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Berni Moestafa in Jakarta at 
